1
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:28,560
Today, I'll show you how to unlock a new skill.

2
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:31,720
This car should be faster than the ones in your time, right?

3
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:32,759
Not necessarily.

4
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:35,120
My driving skills are top-notch.

5
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,920
Tch, I don't believe it.

6
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:39,039
You said it yourself.

7
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,400
You really have to believe me when it comes to driving.

8
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,320
Believe you're an experienced driver.

9
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:45,039
Yeah. That alone is enough.

10
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:46,780
I don't believe it.

11
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,840
Race me if you have the guts.

12
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,160
In this car?

13
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:53,960
Yaoyao, listen to him.

14
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:55,400
Sounds like he's looking down on us.

15
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,960
Then let's have a race.

16
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,020
Bring it on.

17
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,000
Come on, Yiyi!

18
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,320
Come on, Yiyi!

19
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,680
Come on, Yiyi!

20
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,960
Go, go!

21
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,800
Go, Yaoyao!

22
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:38,240
Just like that. Yes.

23
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,360
Yes, charge!

24
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,440
Charge!

25
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:45,840
I won!

26
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,480
This is so fun!

27
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,760
What?

28
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,600
Just fun, not exciting?

29
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,520
Compared to the Burma Road,

30
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,160
this is not exciting at all.

31
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,560
Tch, I was so close to beating you today.

32
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,880
Well, I'm used to being in a hurry.

33
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,140
Shouldn't it be ladies first?

34
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,640
Ladies first.

35
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:11,370
I thought you only cared about winning today.

36
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,840
Oh, it's just a game.

37
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:16,490
There's no difference between men and women.

38
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:21,160
But on the battlefield, there's no distinction between age and gender,

39
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,200
or the old, weak, sick, and disabled.

40
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:23,560
I said we are here to have fun today,

41
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:23,880
I said we are here to have fun today,

42
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:24,040
I said we are here to have fun today,

43
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,760
I said we are here to have fun today,

44
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,420
not to listen to your lecture.

45
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,600
If you had a choice,

46
00:04:33,159 --> 00:04:36,480
would you want to go back to the past or travel to the future?

47
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,920
If it were me,

48
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:48,720
I would definitely choose to go back to the past.

49
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,360
Don't you want to see the future?

50
00:04:55,159 --> 00:04:56,560
You don't get it.

51
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,800
You can find information about the past,

52
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,600
so I would know everything in advance.

53
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,400
If I traveled back,

54
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:05,160
everyone would call me a prophet.

55
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:10,250
You've watched too many time-travel shows, Prophet Zhang.

56
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,960
Don't underestimate me.

57
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,400
If I traveled back,

58
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,120
everyone would swarm around me and ask,

59
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:19,920
'Prophet, when will it rain and when will the wind blow?'

60
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,760
I think you as a prophet,

61
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,820
is quite similar to a fortune teller.

62
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:28,320
Actually, going back to the past with a modern mindset,

63
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,960
does have a huge advantage to some extent.

64
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,400
But have you ever thought

65
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,060
that you might not get used to the life back then?

66
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:37,840
You just reminded me.

67
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,600
According to my experience watching time-travel shows,

68
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,400
I must bring a lot of things

69
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,000
for emergencies.

70
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:46,640
Oh, I'll also bring a bag.

71
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:47,760
When I come back,

72
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,840
I'll bring lots and lots of antiques.

73
00:05:50,159 --> 00:05:51,840
Those are real antiques.

74
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:55,130
They are worth much more than an old antique like you.

75
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:59,400
Yiyi, you're daydreaming.

76
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,680
So is that why you want to go back?

77
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,040
Not entirely.

78
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:13,280
I might need to think about it more.

79
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,140
What about you?

80
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:24,800
Actually, I think it's better to let nature take its course.

81
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:29,560
Past, present, and future are all the same to me.

82
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:32,720
Don't you want to experience it,

83
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,600
to go back and make a fortune like Yiyi?

84
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,600
Why are you picking on me?

85
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,120
I'm me, and she's her.

86
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:41,050
Everyone thinks differently.

87
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:45,720
I think the point of life is the experience.

88
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:49,159
It doesn't matter which stage it's in.

89
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,320
Oh, Yaoyao.

90
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,120
We're just being hypothetical.

91
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:55,050
Why are you taking it so seriously?

92
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:59,600
Yiyi, it's time to wake up from this pipe dream.

93
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:06,400
Then what if I said from now on,

94
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,730
you'll have endless wealth and glory?

95
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,080
But there is a condition.

96
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,530
What condition?

97
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:15,760
Your remaining lifespan will be confiscated starting tomorrow.

98
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:18,600
I knew it. Anything starting with 'if'

99
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,080
won't lead to anything good.

100
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,000
So you're not stupid.

101
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,260
You're the stupid one.

102
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,400
Aren't you just taking a jab at me?

103
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:28,600
You see, his roundabout way

104
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,810
actually made you understand, right?

105
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,159
Oh.

106
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,960
There aren't that many 'ifs'.

107
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:37,600
If there really were that many 'ifs',

108
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,330
there wouldn't be so many failures and setbacks.

109
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,600
They say failure is the mother of success.

110
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,680
But who wants to keep facing setbacks?

111
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,880
The key is, we can't afford to lose.

112
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,440
Yes, you're right.

113
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:54,560
The whole process of growing up is about facing setbacks.

114
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,400
But all experience

115
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,490
comes from trial and error,

116
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,400
and learning lessons.

117
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:02,720
Right.

118
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,060
I watched a movie a couple of days ago.

119
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,720
The lead actor's name was...

120
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,640
something Chi.

121
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,480
I think one of his quotes was very right.

122
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,960
He said, 'I don't want to win.

123
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,860
I just don't want to lose.'

124
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:17,000
Setbacks aren't scary.

125
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,730
A hundred times is fine.

126
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,940
What about the 101st time?

127
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,640
Whether it's 100 or 101 times,

128
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:30,640
what's scary is not having the courage to keep fighting after failure.

129
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,240
Only you, Lin Yaozu.

130
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,480
It's getting late.

131
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:44,480
Let's go.

132
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,360
Let's go.

133
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:47,800
Go.

134
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,340
Are you coming?

135
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,400
Let's go.

136
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,440
Hey, hurry up.

137
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,480
If we win later, it's your treat.
